article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 66, Menlo 44
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Trae Clark scored 17 points and Dreshawn Vance had 14 points and 11 rebounds as Cal Poly beat Menlo 66-44 Sunday. Vance went 4-for-6 from the floor and 6-for-10 from the free-throw line as he scored a season-high and had his first double-double as a Mustang. Lorenzo Keeler added 14 points for Cal Poly (4-3). Bryon Wesley led Menlo (2-4) with nine points. Cal Poly led by as many as 13 in the first half and was up 31-24 at halftime. Menlo then went on a 12-2 run in the second half to tie it at 36 with 13:31 to play. But Clark hit a jumper a minute later that gave Cal Poly the lead for good 38-36, and the Mustangs outscored Menlo 30-8 over the final 13 minutes. Both teams shot under 35 percent from the floor and under 60 percent from the free-throw line.
